In your DNS panel:

Type: A

Host: finalbackend

Value: YOUR_SERVER_PUBLIC_IP

Test:

ping finalbackend.multifolks.com

🐍 BACKEND (Python on port 5000)
3️⃣ Create virtual environment (recommended)
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate

4️⃣ Install Python dependencies

Depending on your repo:

If you have requirements.txt
pip install -r requirements.txt

5️⃣ Run backend locally (test)

Examples:

Flask

python app.py


FastAPI

uvicorn main:app --host 127.0.0.1 --port 5000


Gunicorn (recommended)

gunicorn app:app --bind 127.0.0.1:5000

curl http://127.0.0.1:5000
🌍 Step 6: Connect domain via Nginx
You already did / are doing this part:

final.multifolks.com → React build/

finalbackend.multifolks.com → proxy to localhost:5000

1️⃣ Delete the broken venv

From your backend directory:

deactivate
rm -rf venv

2️⃣ Make sure venv support is installed
sudo apt install python3.12-venv -y

3️⃣ Re-create the virtual environment
python3.12 -m venv venv


Activate it:

source venv/bin/activate

5️⃣ Install requirements (THIS time correctly)
pip install -r requirements.txt


✅ No sudo
✅ No permission errors
✅ No externally-managed-environment error

Run your backend

Example for FastAPI:

uvicorn main:app --host 127.0.0.1 --port 5000


Test:

curl http://127.0.0.1:5000

🚀 Next (production-ready)

Once this runs, I recommend:

Run with gunicorn

Add systemd service

Proxy with Nginx → finalbackend.multifolks.com

https://chatgpt.com/#:~:text=%E2%9D%8C%20If%20you%20see%20root,home/technology/backend/newbackend

4️⃣ Reinstall venv support (safe)
sudo apt install python3.12-venv python3.12-dev build-essential -y


(Some packages like cryptography need this)

5️⃣ Create venv AGAIN (no sudo)
python3.12 -m venv venv


Activate:

source venv/bin/activate


Confirm:

which python


Should point to:

.../venv/bin/python

6️⃣ Upgrade pip (inside venv)
pip install --upgrade pip setuptools wheel

7️⃣ Install requirements (NO sudo)
pip install -r requirements.txt


✅ This will now work.

🔁 STEP 5: Run backend with Gunicorn (production)

(Example for FastAPI)

pip install gunicorn
gunicorn main:app --bind 127.0.0.1:5000 --workers 2


Test again:

curl http://127.0.0.1:5000


Stop:

CTRL + C

⚙️ STEP 6: Create systemd service (auto-start)
sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/finalbackend.service


Paste (adjust app name if needed):

[Unit]
Description=Final Backend API
After=network.target

[Service]
User=technology
Group=technology
WorkingDirectory=/home/technology/backend/newbackend
Environment="PATH=/home/technology/backend/newbackend/venv/bin"
ExecStart=/home/technology/backend/newbackend/venv/bin/gunicorn main:app --bind 127.0.0.1:5000 --workers 2
Restart=always

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target


Save.

Enable & start:

sudo systemctl daemon-reexec
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable finalbackend
sudo systemctl start finalbackend


Check:

sudo systemctl status finalbackend


🌐 STEP 8: Nginx reverse proxy
sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/finalbackend.multifolks.com


Paste:

server {
    listen 80;
    server_name finalbackend.multifolks.com;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:5000;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;

        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
    }
}


Enable:

sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/finalbackend.multifolks.com /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/
sudo nginx -t
sudo systemctl reload nginx


Test:
👉 http://finalbackend.multifolks.com

🔒 STEP 9: HTTPS (SSL)
sudo certbot --nginx -d finalbackend.multifolks.com


Choose:
✔ Redirect HTTP → HTTPS

Final:
👉 https://finalbackend.multifolks.com

